Removes sections from each SKILL.md that duplicate work the agent already
does. SKILL.md keeps the router-level content (Overview, routing table,
Use_When, Do_Not_Use_When, high-level Steps); agents keep the execution
contract, tool choices, checklists, and reference lists.

Removed from SKILL.md (present in corresponding agent):
- Companion_Skills          — long list of related skills, noise at router
- Tool_Usage                — implementation detail
- References                — agent loads these on demand
- Final_Checklist           — post-planning validation belongs in agent
- Perspectives              (drupal-critic) — review lens, agent-level
- Drupal-Specific Must-Check List (drupal-critic)
- Skill Loading Rules       (drupal-critic)
- Severity Calibration      (drupal-critic)
- Stop Conditions           (drupal-critic)
- Required Output Contract  (drupal-critic)
- Input Modes               (drupal-config-executor)
- Resolution Paths          (drupal-config-executor)
- What You Get              (drupal-config-executor)
- meta-router Registry Note (drupal-config-executor)

Measurement (char/4 estimator):
- SKILL.md total: 8,807 -> 5,891 tokens (-33%)
- Turn-10 parent context:  9,307 -> 6,391 tokens (-31%)

The bundle already achieves 83% parent-context savings vs the flattened
straw-man via its existing SKILL.md-routes-to-agent pattern. This patch
closes another ~31% by removing content from SKILL.md that belongs in
the agent anyway.

No Agent files changed — the routing contract is unchanged, and clients
calling `Agent(subagent_type=...)` continue to get the full protocol.

Full analysis: https://github.com/zivtech/claude-cost-helpers
See meta-router-analysis/benchmark/results.md and
meta-router-analysis/improvements/router-v2-spec.md.
